HEADWORD: flowers-of-an-hour
<hw>flowers-of-an-hour</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An annual weedy herb
(<spn>Hibiscus trionum</spn>) with ephemeral yellow purple-eyed flowers,
native to the Old World tropics and naturalized as a weed in North
America.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> flower-of-an-hour, bladder ketmia, black-eyed Susan,
<spn>Hibiscus trionum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

